<TITLE> Business wants Tk 6000 cr recession fund </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Mar 15 (bdnews24.com)--Business leaders say they estimate a Tk 6,000 crore (60 billion) "stimulus package" will be required to fight global recession. In a meeting with prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Sunday, FBCCI leaders recommended such a package to save sagging exports to the recession-ridden world markets, president Annisul Huq said. "Bangladesh's key exports such as readymade garments, jute, leather, frozen foods have begun bearing the brunt," Huq told bdnews24.com after the meeting. He claimed the prime minister responded positively to their demand. However, a top spokesperson to Sheikh Hasina did not mention the size of the package during a briefing on the PM-FBCCI meeting. The business leaders also sought to convince the prime minister about lowering the lending rates and making Sunday the weekly holiday, instead of Frid
